body:
Too many champs, not enough bans, not enough nerfs on champions who are polarizing the meta in a negative way, riot balance team with not enough played time on their own game (thanks ghostcrawler), and simply put, there's no reason to keep expanding the champ pool without increasing these. You did it once before, do it again. Next season 20 bans. Ban phase before first pick, then another after the second pair of players pick their champions.

Make it happen. We don't want to ban {{champion:84}} just to get {{champion:142}} 
or ban {{champion:104}} just to get {{champion:203}} who is just as if not in some ways more broken than the former
or ban {{champion:266}} just to get {{champion:39}} 
or ban {{champion:555}} just to get {{champion:63}} 
or ban {{champion:202}} just to go against {{champion:21}}  
we want real variety in games, and want to really hit on the head who needs nerfs by who's banned.

